{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name =20,000 Years of Fashion: The History of Costume and Personal Adornment | image =20,000 Years of Fashion by Boucher.jpg | image_size = | alt = | caption = Bottom half of book cover with details from colored plates | author = [[Francois Boucher (art historian)|Francois Boucher]] & [[Yvonne Deslandres]] | audio_read_by = | title_orig = | orig_lang_code = | title_working = | translator = | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United Kingdom, France, United States | language = English, French | series = | release_number = | subject = | genre = [[Art history]] | set_in = | published = | publisher = [[Abrams Books|Harry N Abrams]] | publisher2 = [[Groupe Flammarion]] | pub_date = 1963-66, 1987 | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = 441 | awards = | isbn = | oclc = 176250 | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = | native_wikisource = | wikisource = | notes = | exclude_cover = }}
'''''20,000 Years of Fashion: The History of Costume and Personal Adornment''''' is a dictionary of western fashion from ancient times up to the 1960s, edited by [[Francois Boucher (art historian)|Francois Boucher]] and his longtime assistant [[Yvonne Deslandres]].
The book is widely cited as a reference for fashion trends in paintings and has 1150 illustrations which are mostly paintings, etchings and engravings from Western museums and collections. The book includes a glossary of terms and a bibliography of sources. It was originally published in French in 1965 as ''Histoire du Costume en Occident de l’antiquité à nos jours'' and was translated into English the next year, but was published after Boucher's death. In 1987 Deslandres updated a new edition with a section on modern fashion.
