{{for|the market in Frankfurt, Germany|Frankfurt Christmas Market}} [[File:Frankfurt Christmas Market IM1331 New Street C.JPG|thumb|View of the market at night in [[New Street, Birmingham]].]] [[File:Birmingham Weihnachtsmarkt - geograph.org.uk - 92000.jpg|thumb|Daytime view.]]
The '''Frankfurt Christmas Market and Craft Market''' is an annual outdoor [[Christmas market]] and [[craft fair]] held in central [[Birmingham]], [[England]].<ref name="visitbirmingham">{{cite web| url=http://visitbirmingham.com/birminghams-frankfurt-christmas-market/ | title=Birmingham's Frankfurt Christmas Market & Craft Fair | website=[VisitBirmingham] | accessdate=22 December 2014 }}</ref> The market started in 2001 with 24 stalls and has slowly expanded every year.<ref name="birminghamnewsroom">{{cite web| url=http://birminghamnewsroom.com/another-record-year-for-frankfurt-christmas-market/ | title=Another record year for Frankfurt Christmas Market | website=[BirminghamNewsroom] | accessdate=13 November 2015 }}</ref> It opens in mid November and continues until late December, closing just before [[Christmas]].
The Christmas Market and Craft Fair is located in [[Centenary Square]], [[Chamberlain Square]], [[New Street, Birmingham|New Street]], and [[Victoria Square, Birmingham|Victoria Square]].<ref name="visitbirmingham" /> It is the largest such market outside [[Germany]] and [[Austria]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.enjoyengland.com/attractions/events/calendar/december/christmas-markets.aspx |title=Christmas markets |publisher=Enjoy England |accessdate=11 October 2010 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090908041448/http://www.enjoyengland.com/attractions/events/calendar/december/christmas-markets.aspx |archivedate=September 8, 2009 }}</ref> attracting over 3.1 million visitors in 2010,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.birminghamnewsroom.com/?p=6019|title=Another Record year for Frankfurt Christmas Market|publisher=Birmingham City Council|accessdate=29 September 2010}}</ref> over 5 million visitors in 2011,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.birminghammail.net/news/top-stories/2012/07/27/birmingham-s-frankfurt-christmas-market-will-be-back-november-15-december-22-97319-31487142/|title=Birmingham's Frankfurt Christmas Market will be back November 15-December 22|publisher=Birmingham Mail|accessdate=18 September 2012}}</ref> almost 5 million visitors in 2013<ref>{{cite web| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-birmingham-30006242 | title=Birmingham Christmas Frankfurt Market: How German is it? | website=[[BBC News]] | publisher=[[BBC]] | location=UK | date=15 November 2014 | accessdate=22 December 2014 }}</ref> and over 5.5 million visitors in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-birmingham-31638143|title=Birmingham's German Market sees 'record number' of visitors|publisher=BBC News|date=26 February 2015|accessdate=26 October 2015}}</ref> German food and drink such as [[Bratwurst]] sausages and warm [[Glühwein]] are available.
The market is affiliated with the [[Frankfurt Christmas Market]] in the city of [[Frankfurt]],<ref name="frankfurt-tourismus">{{cite web| url=http://www.germany-insider-facts.com/frankfurt-christmas-market.html | title=Frankfurt Christmas Market | website=germany-insider-facts.com/ | accessdate=22 December 2014 }}</ref> one of the oldest such markets in Germany (dating from 1393), hence the name.
The market will run from 17 November until 29 December 2016, from 10am to 9pm each day, excluding Christmas Day itself, and will contain in excess of 180 stalls.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.birminghammail.co.uk/whats-on/whats-on-news/birminghams-german-market-back-2016-11364945 | title=Birmingham’s German Market is back for 2016 - and will be staying over Christmas for the first time ever | website=birminghammail.co.uk | date=13 October 2016 }}</ref>
